The subject introduces students to the chosen field of chemistry and the opportunities for the future. Excursions to the teaching and research laboratories of the Institute of Chemistry. Employers' representatives meet with students and study visits to various chemistry-related companies.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give chemistry students a comprehensive view of the nature of the future specialty, the requirements to be submitted and the specialty related perspectives.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student 1. is aware of the research work carried out by various scientific groups of the Institute of Chemistry and is able to choose the appropriate research direction for the final thesis 2. is familiar with the professors supervising the research groups and the basic instructions for the final theses 3. Plans its own timetable, which allows the practical part of the thesis to be carried out in parallel with the compulsory study 4. Select a company if possible, get acquainted with the work there, to do professional practice 5. knows what jobs can be found on the labor market after completing the chemistry curriculum
